textline.data: The system should inform nearby cars
of a danger situation
The maximum delay from danger detection
to msg broadcast should be 150 ms
The system should detect a danger coming
from the ECU of the chassis
The warning message should contain different
information: longitude, latitude, altitude,
speed, acceleration and heading of the car,
Commands should be send to the powertrain
to get helpful drivin power adjustments
Commands should be send to the actuator
ECU in the chassis
The system should communicate with
others ECU inside the car
Whenever a disengage manoeuvre
has been performed, the system should
send a message to the nearby cars
The system should avoid accidents due to
danger-avoid manoeuvre
All message to and from the CU have the same
Internal failures are not taken into account.
Subsystems are supposed to be online and
to work correctly all the time
Actions required by the actuators and the
powertrain are not modelled
The message to the actuator ECUs after a danger situation
has been detected, is sent to only one ECU which will route
the command to the right actuator
The messages between subsystems of
car and to the nearby car are not repeated:
loss of messages is not allowed
